topicID=197.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Weird PoP Mob Behavior</span><hr size=1> I have been soloing trees and ravens in PoN as of late and had a couple of wierd things happen:<br>
<br>
1) Mob &quot;Gates&quot; at low hp. No cast, just kinda repops back at spawn point.<br>
<br>
2) Mobs loses aggro at very low hp.<br>
<br>
In both cases, this typically causes the mob to regen its hp extremely fast (non-combat regen?) and can cause a nasty surprise for the attacker if he comes across it again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhionsligo>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1296<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 1:30:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=197.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/starofdavid.gif width=36 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weird PoP Mob Behavior</span><hr size=1> This is a bug common with many outdoor zones.  It was most prominent with the releast of velious.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of problems with outdoor zones. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=106710"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
My Character Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=perelandraeldil>Perelandra Eldil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 1:33:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=197.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weird PoP Mob Behavior</span><hr size=1> I've soloed a lot in outdoor zones - including Velious - and never had this happen. It happens pretty much every time in PoN such that I have to fight the mob on it's spawn point.<br>
<br>
Maybe it just takes me so much longer to kill PoN mobs I never noticed it before. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhasinfirestorm@themagicianstower>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1278<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 6:23:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=197.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weird PoP Mob Behavior</span><hr size=1> This behavior happens a LOT when there is noone within nearby range (not necessarily in melee, but close by) and the mob starts to run. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886&quot;"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ninjacorp.com/Rhasin_sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flaamwing>Flaamwing</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 7:26:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=197.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weird PoP Mob Behavior</span><hr size=1> It's distance based when they go into flee mode.<br>
<br>
I've seen it in PoN, PoD, and now PoV - when I kite or root/dot mobs this happens.  Flee mode appears to depend on how many HPs the mob has compared to you.  But once they enter flee mode, if you are not within the original agro distance (i.e. how close can you get to one of these without casting before it agros to begin with) then it starts to heal as if agro is lost.<br>
<br>
Once it heals beyond flee mode, it always reacquires me.  I dont know if this is due to the dot's on it or if it would do this without gaining agro again.<br>
<br>
But its easy to stop this happening, just stay slightly outside of melee range once it gets down in HPs and close to flee mode.<br>
<br>
Flaamwing - 64th Necro of Bristlebane<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~coderjohn/AllChars.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104338">Flaamwings gear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=soulcraver>Soulcraver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 7:41:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=197.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   behavior</span><hr size=1> This happened a ton in BoT this morning.  And if you've fought in BoT you know the mobs don't flee and the mobs were engage 100% of the time.<br>
<br>
This is new behavior (as far as frequency) that I noticed this morning.<br>
<br>
We had a kick ass group so it didn't matter much but was just generally annoying at times. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eatbugs>Eatbugs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#333333>(2/11/03 7:14:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=197.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: behavior</span><hr size=1> Great Divide is infamous for the flee mode warp - unless you (not the pet) are right up near a mob when it goes into flee mode, it will warp back to its spawn point.<br>
<br>
Used to bug the heck out of me as a Druid, particularly with the sudden spectacular regen.  Never had a problem there as a Beastlord, since I was almost always in melee range. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=veganus>Veganus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(2/12/03 1:15:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=197.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: behavior</span><hr size=1> As a Wizard this happens very often while kiting if the mob goes into flee mode and you aren t very near like melee range 8(, it s one of the most annoying bugs and is around since forever i think<br>
